        "title": "feat(anthropic): support Claude Fable 5 adaptive thinking",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- add Claude Fable 5 to the Anthropic and Anthropic Vertex catalogs with its 1M context window, 128k output limit, multimodal input, and pricing metadata\n- centralize the model's always-adaptive thinking contract, including effort mapping, unsupported sampling/tool-choice normalization, and model-bound thinking replay\n- handle structured refusals and partial-output quarantine consistently across the direct provider and transport paths\n- keep the implementation bounded by shared provider/model helpers; production changes are 752 additions and 250 deletions, while most of the diff is regression coverage\n- document direct API and Vertex usage\n\nFixes #91805.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/agents/anthropic-transport-stream.test.ts src/llm/providers/anthropic.test.ts extensions/anthropic/index.test.ts extensions/anthropic-vertex/stream-runtime.test.ts`\n  - 122 tests passed after the final rebase onto `origin/main`\n- AWS Crabbox broad validation: https://crabbox.openclaw.ai/portal/runs/run_2f28fbb00c37\n  - runtime guards and import-cycle checks passed\n  - 301 selected regression tests passed across four shards\n- AWS Crabbox live Anthropic validation: https://crabbox.openclaw.ai/portal/runs/run_9a73b8acd7ff\n  - fresh remote build passed\n  - real `anthropic/claude-fable-5` calls passed for `--thinking high` and logical `--thinking off`\n  - both calls returned the exact requested marker with provider `anthropic`, model `claude-fable-5`, and no fallback\n- fresh autoreview completed with no actionable findings\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Claude Fable 5 works through the Anthropic provider with its required adaptive-thinking request shape, model metadata, replay rules, and refusal handling; Anthropic Vertex uses the same model contract.\n\nReal environment tested: AWS Crabbox Linux `c7a.8xlarge` with a real Anthropic API credential.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: built the synced checkout, then ran `node openclaw.mjs agent --local --model anthropic/claude-fable-5 --thinking high ... --json` and the same command with `--thinking off`.\n\nEvidence after fix: https://crabbox.openclaw.ai/portal/runs/run_9a73b8acd7ff\n\nObserved result after fix: both live calls returned exactly `FABLE_CRABBOX_OK`; execution metadata reported Anthropic/Fable 5 and `fallbackUsed: false`.\n\nWhat was not tested: live Anthropic Vertex credentials were not exercised. Vertex catalog/transport behavior and structured refusal streams are covered by focused regression tests.\n\n## Release note\n\nAnthropic: add Claude Fable 5 support for direct API and Vertex, including adaptive thinking, 1M context, 128k output, safe replay, and refusal handling.\n",
